{"lemma":"شُعْلَةٌ","slug":"شُعْلَةٌ","root":"ش.ع.ل","root_slug":"ش-ع-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ع-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22512"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8F%D8%B9%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a flame"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a firebrand, a piece of wood in which fire is kindled"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʃuʕ.la/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22512","headword_ar":"شُعْلَةٌ","root":"$El","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A firebrand; a piece of wood in which fire is kindled;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, K, * TA;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ji*owapN","text_ar":"جِذْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qayasN","text_ar":"قَيَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ihaAbN","text_ar":"شِهَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Az, TA:) [this is what is meant by its being said that] what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEolapN mino naArK","text_ar":"شُعْلَةٌ مِنْ نَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the only indication of the meaning in the S and O] is well known: (Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEalN","text_ar":"شُعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, TA;) erroneously said in the K to be like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kutubN","text_ar":"كُتُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN $uEolapu naArK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ شُعْلَةُ نَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is a firebrand"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Er-Rághib, TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akaA='N","text_ar":"ذَكَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.) ―         -b2-  And ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lighted wick:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the present day: (see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEiylapN","text_ar":"شَعِيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burnt"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lighted"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity of a wick."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiraATN","text_ar":"قِرَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". [And the same meaning is intended there in the K; and also in the TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ji*owapN","text_ar":"جِذْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b3-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flame of fire;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEoluwlN","text_ar":"شُعْلُولٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, * TA. [In the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEuwl","text_ar":"شُعُول"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as though it were a second pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEolapN","text_ar":"شُعْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEolapu","text_ar":"شُعْلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K, TA,) without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) is the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mare of Keys Ibn-Sebáa;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA;) likened to the kindling of fire, because of her swiftness. (TA.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEalN","text_ar":"شَعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":["Az","TA","Msb","O","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}